post_text:
Final information before we start school:

The Wellness Certification form is really important. Please watch the video that has been put on Facebook or the school website for directions.

1. All students must have a completed wellness screening to enter the building or get on the school bus.

2. All bus riders must have a paper form of this to hand to their bus driver.

3. If your student doesn't ride a bus, you can complete the wellness screening on Skyward. There will be an icon called "Wellness Screening".

4. For Friday, August 21, simply write a note if you are not able to print a copy of the Wellness Screening paper. On Friday, the teachers will send home paper copies of the Wellness Screening to use in the future.

post_text:
Reminder for Face Coverings
• All individuals (child and adult) in school buildings and bus riders, must wear face coverings at all times unless they are younger than two years of age; have trouble breathing, or are unconscious, incapacitated, or otherwise unable to remove the cover without assistance.
• Face coverings must be worn at all times in school buildings and buses even when social distancing is maintained. Face coverings do not need to be worn outside if social distancing is maintained.
• If a student or staff member is unable to wear a face-covering due to a medical reason (i.e. trouble breathing, etc.) a physician’s note must be provided to the school.

post_text: Oblong and Palestine Football jerseys are being sold to raise money for Sports Boosters.
shared_text:
Nick Straka‎OPH Stronger Together Football Fan Page
July 11 at 12:16 PM ·

OPH Faithful,

Spread the word that we are now hosting an online sale for old Oblong and Palestine/Hutsonville jerseys. All proceeds go to the school's sports boosters. There are quite a few jerseys to select from but the total number is unclear. Attached are pictures of some of the jerseys we have. All jerseys start at $10 each. It is unclear what numbers are available at this time outside of those listed. I will be sure to post a list of what is available at a later date.

If you wish to see the jerseys we are at Oblong HS Wednesday the 15th from 4-5 PM. I can also schedule additional days if we have multiple people interested. If there is a number you are interested in please let me know and I will note it and look when I am back in the locker room.

This is a great opportunity to support the sports booster so please spread the word!

Thank you,
Coach Straka
Go OPH

A great big THANK YOU to everyone for their contributions for the Soldier care package drive!
We received enough donations to send 50 care packages to our troops overseas.

Thanks for your help in making this possible!
It was delayed a little due to the virus but are now in the mail.

Unit 4 parent/guardians:
At the current time we cannot have Kindergarten screenings, and we cannot say when that may be possible.

If you have student that will be entering Kindergarten in the fall of 2020, we would like for you to contact our principal, Mrs. Meese.
You may email mmeese@oblongschools.net with the child’s name, date of birth, and street address, state whether you would like the paperwork sent to you. If you opt to receive paperwork, we will mail it to you and you will return to us by mail. Please email within the next few weeks.
All Kindergarten parents will report to our in person registration in August (date cannot be confirmed at this time) unless we have been allowed to have screenings.
We will do our best to keep you informed as more information becomes available. Thank you for patience and understanding.

Attention 5th grade band:
If you need to return your instrument:
1. Please call The Music Shoppe 800-842-0035
This is to let them know you want to stop the rental payment and the instrument will be returned. This MUST be done before you return the instrument.

2. Return the instrument to one of two places. You may bring the instrument to the school sometime this week when you pick up your students belongings. You may also take your instrument to The Blue Potato in Oblong. They are now partnering with The Music Shoppe and will get the instrument where it needs to go.

3. Email me that you have called The Music Shoppe so I know you are planning to return the instrument and let me know where you dropped it off.

Thank you!!

Reminder:
Each day this week, from 10:30-11:30, there will be plastic storage containers set out by the Grade School Office for OES students to drop off their completed school work up to this point. The containers are clearly labeled with each teachers name. Please pull up to the containers, get out of your car and place your materials in the appropriate container.
There is also a red container for library books. If you have a library book at home that you are finished with please go ahead and return it.
There is also a container for Junior High track uniforms. Please put your uniform in a plastic bag or ziploc bag and write your name on the bag and drop your uniform into the container.
Another drop off will be scheduled in May.

Gina Mills COUNTRY Financial
February 21 at 11:36 AM ·

Congratulations to Ava Manuel for winning the Crawford County Artist of the Month for February! Ava is the daughter of Audrey and Zach Manuel and an 8th grader at Oblong Grade School. She has been in Art for 10 years and is a very talented artist, having some of her artwork displayed in the Children’s Art Show at Lincoln Trail College. She also takes piano lessons and plays the ukulele.

According to Ms. Wilson, “Ava is an excellent student and an amazing leader. She is always ready to help out her peers and any teacher that needs help with something. She is very kind, responsible, mature, respectful, and very talented.”

Please help us congratulate Ava for winning this award!
#CCArtistoftheMonth

post_text:
Unit 4 families: Just a reminder students return to school on Tuesday, January 7th.
We hope everyone has enjoyed their winter break and we look forward to seeing everyone.

As we return, remember cold and flu season is upon us. If you haven’t already, we recommend taking some time in the next two days to make sure your student’s coats, hats, gloves, lunch boxes and backpacks have been washed and cleaned. This will help prevent germs from spreading.
If your child has been ill, remember they can not attend school until they have been fever free for 24 hours (includes vomiting and diarrhea also) Please be in contact with our nurse, Valerie Ping should you have any further questions upon return!

We look forward to seeing all of the students on Tuesday, January 7th for happy and healthy second semester.
